\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{index::doc}}


Welcome to the Project’s documentation!

This is a documentation for the source code to the web application for \sphinxstylestrong{Best-Worst-Scaling}. The source code includes scripts for frontend and backend.

Backend is mainly developed with \sphinxhref{https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-369/}{Python3.6} using \sphinxhref{https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/1.1.x/}{Flask} and its extensions. The application is also integrated with Amazon Crowdsourcing Platform using its \sphinxhref{https://boto3.amazonaws.com/v1/documentation/api/latest/guide/quickstart.html}{API}.

For the frontend development, besides \sphinxhref{https://www.w3schools.com/html/default.asp}{HTML}, \sphinxhref{https://www.w3schools.com/css/default.asp}{CSS}, \sphinxhref{https://www.w3schools.com/js/default.asp}{JavaScript} and \sphinxhref{https://getbootstrap.com/}{Bootstrap4}, \sphinxhref{https://jinja.palletsprojects.com/en/2.11.x/}{Jinja2} is used for dynamic rendering of the most of the templates.

\index{generate\_tuples() (project.generator.DataGenerator method)@\spxentry{generate\_tuples()}\spxextra{project.generator.DataGenerator method}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{project_rst/generator:project.generator.DataGenerator.generate_tuples}}\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{generate\_tuples}}}{}{}
Generate tuples, this is a reimplementation of \sphinxtitleref{generate-BWS-tuples.pl}
in \sphinxhref{https://saifmohammad.com/WebDocs/Best-Worst-Scaling-Scripts.zip}{source code}.

The tuples are generated by random sampling and satisfy the following
criteria:
\begin{enumerate}
\sphinxsetlistlabels{\arabic}{enumi}{enumii}{}{.}%
\item {} 
no two items within a tuple are identical;

\item {} 
each item in the item list appears approximately in the same number of tuples;

\item {} 
each pair of items appears approximately in the same number of tuples.

\end{enumerate}
\begin{quote}\begin{description}
\item[{Returns}] \leavevmode
update list of all unique generated tuples with the best results
after all (attribute {\hyperref[\detokenize{project_rst/generator:project.generator.DataGenerator.tuples}]{\sphinxcrossref{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{tuples}}}}}).

\item[{Return type}] \leavevmode
\sphinxhref{https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html\#list}{list}

\item[{Raises}] \leavevmode
\sphinxhref{https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html\#ValueError}{\sphinxstyleliteralstrong{\sphinxupquote{ValueError}}} \textendash{} if the number of {\hyperref[\detokenize{project_rst/generator:project.generator.DataGenerator.items}]{\sphinxcrossref{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{items}}}}} is fewer than {\hyperref[\detokenize{project_rst/generator:project.generator.DataGenerator.tuple_size}]{\sphinxcrossref{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{tuple\_size}}}}}.

\end{description}\end{quote}

\end{fulllineitems}


\end{fulllineitems}

\subsubsection{Validators}
\label{\detokenize{project_rst/validators:module-project.validators}}\label{\detokenize{project_rst/validators:validators}}\label{\detokenize{project_rst/validators::doc}}\index{project.validators (module)@\spxentry{project.validators}\spxextra{module}}
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Module} \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{project.validators}}

This module provides validators for all forms used within all systems.
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Call the classes the same way with classes in Module \sphinxhref{https://wtforms.readthedocs.io/en/latest/validators.html\#}{wtforms.validators}.

\item {} 
Use functions mostly inside overwritten \sphinxhref{https://wtforms.readthedocs.io/en/latest/forms.html\#wtforms.form.Form.validate}{validate()}
or \sphinxhref{https://wtforms.readthedocs.io/en/latest/forms.html\#wtforms.form.Form.validate}{validate\_\textless{}fieldname\textgreater{}()}.

\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Annotator Subsystem}
\label{\detokenize{project_rst/annotator_rst/annotator:module-project.annotator.__init__}}\label{\detokenize{project_rst/annotator_rst/annotator:annotator-subsystem}}\label{\detokenize{project_rst/annotator_rst/annotator::doc}}\index{project.annotator.\_\_init\_\_ (module)@\spxentry{project.annotator.\_\_init\_\_}\spxextra{module}}
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Subpackage} \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{project.annotator}}

This subpackage defines Annotator-System for annotators to annotate datas.
\begin{description}
\item[{Main functions:}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Login

\item {} 
View all batches

\item {} 
Annotate batch

\end{itemize}

\item[{Two \sphinxhref{https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/1.1.x/blueprints/}{Blueprints} define two annotator systems:}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Local: at \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{/annotator}}

\item {} 
With \sphinxhref{https://www.mturk.com/}{Mechanical Turk}: at \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{/mturk}}

\end{itemize}

\end{description}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{project_rst/annotator_rst/forms:module-project.annotator.forms}}\index{project.annotator.forms (module)@\spxentry{project.annotator.forms}\spxextra{module}}

\index{is\_not\_current\_user() (in module project.user.helpers)@\spxentry{is\_not\_current\_user()}\spxextra{in module project.user.helpers}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{project_rst/user_rst/helpers:project.user.helpers.is_not_current_user}}\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{project.user.helpers.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{is\_not\_current\_user}}}{\emph{user}, \emph{current\_name}}{}
Inside the User-System, if a user is logged in and authenticated,
this user is not allowed to see profile of an another user by typing the route!
If this meets the conditions which means the current user tries to access to
the account of an another user, this current user will be redirected to the login page
and asked to log in with the used username.
\begin{quote}\begin{description}
\item[{Parameters}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxstyleliteralstrong{\sphinxupquote{user}} (\sphinxhref{https://werkzeug.palletsprojects.com/en/1.0.x/local/\#werkzeug.local.LocalProxy}{werkzeug.LocalProxy}) \textendash{} this is actually
the attribute \sphinxhref{https://flask-login.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\#flask\_login.current\_user}{current\_user}

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleliteralstrong{\sphinxupquote{current\_name}} (\sphinxhref{https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html\#str}{\sphinxstyleliteralemphasis{\sphinxupquote{str}}}) \textendash{} name of the other user to be typed in the route

\end{itemize}

\item[{Returns}] \leavevmode
\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{True}} if this is not the current user else \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{False}}

\item[{Return type}] \leavevmode
\sphinxhref{https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html\#bool}{bool}

\end{description}\end{quote}

\end{fulllineitems}
